 Further, in the performance of the DPP's functions and in the exercise of the DPP's powers, the DPP is subject to such directions or guidelines as the Attorney-General, after consultation with the DPP, gives or furnishes to the DPP by instrument in writi
ng (s\~8(1)).  Those directions or guidelines may be given or furnished in relation to particular cases (s\~8(2)(c)) and may relate to the circumstances in which the DPP shall institute or carry on prosecutions for offences (s\~8(2)(a)).
