\ls5\adjustright \fs26\lang2057\cgrid {KIRBY J.   In }{\i R v Duncan; Ex parte Australian Iron and Steel Pty Ltd}{\cs21\b\super \chftn {\footnote \pard\plain \s20\qj\fi-454\li1021\sa240\sl-280\slmult0\widctlpar
\tx510\tx1021\tx1559\tx2126\tx2693{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \lang2057\cgrid {\cs21\b\fs22 \chftn }{ \tab (1983) 158 CLR 535 at 560 (hereafter "}{\i Duncan}{").}}}{, Mason\~J observed:
\par }\pard\plain \s28\qj\li1134\sa280\sl-280\slmult0\widctlpar\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \fs26\lang3081\cgrid {
"A federal constitution which divides legislative powers between the central legislature and the constituent legi
